snippet: A grandmother of Christine C. Quinn, the City Council speaker and a presumptive mayoral candidate, survived the Titanic to immigrate to America.
abstract: Jim Dwyer About New York column; City Council speaker and presumptive mayoral candidate Christine C Quinn's grandmother Ellen Shine Callaghan, known as Nellie, survived the Titanic disaster to immigrate to America.
lead_paragraph: A grandmother of Christine C. Quinn, the City Council speaker and a presumptive mayoral candidate, survived the Titanic to immigrate to America.

headline.main: Titanic Ties in the Race for Mayor
